{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Creatures üëπüõ¥","author":"Joshua Sheridan"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c07b3054-b831-5724-91c3-d8cdcc40ffc9","excerpt":" In this post I will cover the history of developing the hardware solution for my scooter share app.  üò° Challenges There are two main‚Ä¶","html":"<p> In this post I will cover the history of developing the hardware solution for my scooter share app. </p>\n<h1>üò° Challenges</h1>\n<p>There are two main challenges that I faced in developing my dock-less scooter hardware, tracking and security. Depending on how completely you want to solve these challenges, will determine the approach you take towards implementing a solution.</p>\n<p><strong>Tracking:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Know where the scooter is at all times, as best I can.</li>\n<li>Tracking is needed, because scooters will need to be picked up for charging, and repairs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Security:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>To prevent unauthorized access to the scooter.</li>\n<li>Security is needed to deter thieves and general meanies from harming our beloved scooters.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>ü§î Solutions</h1>\n<h2>üó∫Ô∏è Tracking:</h2>\n<p>I can solve the challenge of tracking though the use of a combination of GPS and a cellular data connection. Below is three methods for tracking, in practice I will be using a combination of two or more of these methods.</p>\n<h3>üìª Embedded GPS on the scooter</h3>\n<p>This method uses a device embedded onto the scooter. The device requires at least a GPS module, GPS antenna, and a cellular data connection to upload the scooter‚Äôs coordinates to our server.</p>\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tracking is physically bound to the scooter.</li>\n<li>Can track even if the scooter is moved when locked.</li>\n<li>Most accurate form of tracking.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Most expensive.</li>\n<li>Largest hardware requirement.</li>\n<li>Requires GPS signal to work.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>üì± User‚Äôs phone GPS</h3>\n<p>Via the <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation_API\">HTML Geolocation API</a> I can request the location of our users. The idea is that I would start tracking once a scooter is checked out and stop once the ride ends. </p>\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Free.</li>\n<li>No requirements for additional scooter hardware.</li>\n<li>The Geolocation API also uses WiFi and IP based locating if GPS signal is not available.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Relies on user‚Äôs cellular connection, which may be unreliable.</li>\n<li>Use of a VPN may prevent accurate tracking.</li>\n<li>Assumes that the phone which unlocked the scooter is within close proximity to the scooter during the entire ride‚Ä¶ which is not necessarily true.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>üì∂ Triangulation of Cell Towers:</h3>\n<p>A device which has a cellular connection can preform a rudimentary form of <a href=\"https://docs.particle.io/tutorials/integrations/google-maps/\">tracking by triangulating it‚Äôs location in relation to nearby cell towers</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mild hardware requirements.</li>\n<li>Works in areas that do not have a GPS signal e.g. indoors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tracking is not very accurate.</li>\n<li>Still requires a device with a cellular connection.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>üëÆ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Security:</h2>\n<p>There are two methods for hopefully keeping the scooters a bit safer.</p>\n<h3>üö® Alarm</h3>\n<p>I want my device to be able to ask and answer this question, <em>Is someone riding me or moving me without permission?</em>  The first requirement to answering this question is that my scooter needs to be able to detect motion.</p>\n<p><strong>Some methods to detect motion:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Embedded accelerometer - detect acceleration.</li>\n<li>Changes in location via GPS.</li>\n<li>Magnetometer - digital compass, detecting changes in direction.</li>\n<li>Use a simple shake switch to detect vibrations.</li>\n<li>Detect if our scooter‚Äôs wheels are moving.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once the device has detected motion, it will check its lock status, if unlocked do nothing, otherwise sound an alarm.</p>\n<h3>üîí Locking</h3>\n<p>I will lock my scooter by disabling the throttle, in affect acting as a remote kill switch.\nFor this to work, my scooter will have an embedded micro controller which will connect to the throttle of the scooter, and control access to it. </p>\n<p><strong>There are several methods that I can provide for a user to unlock the scooter:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Unlock via web app</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Easiest for a user to use.</li>\n<li>Requires active cell connection for our scooter‚Äôs hardware.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Keypad Unlocking</strong> - Turning throttle on or off via keypad on scooter, user would have to enter an unlock code generated by our web app.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Does not require Cell Connection on scooter.</li>\n<li>Would require code to keep security keys in sync on the server and scooter hardware.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bluetooth_Low_Energy\">BLE</a> Unlocking</strong> - Turning throttle on or off via bluetooth, in effect I would use the user‚Äôs bluetooth connection on their phone to control the throttle on the scooter.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Requires a scooter with a cracked BLE protocol.</li>\n<li>In order to use a customer‚Äôs Bluetooth connection, I would need to develop native apps, IOS or Andriod. There is a <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.corg/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Bluetooth_API\">web bluetooth api</a>, however it is not fully supported yet.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>üôÇ Implementation</h1>\n<p>Now that I have my solutions researched, how can I implement the solutions in practice?\nIn the end I came up with two separate hardware solutions,</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A quick and dirty option, that utilizes a cell phone, and minimal effort.</li>\n<li>And a more robust option in which I put together a custom embedded device.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The minimal effort option.</h2>\n<p>The beauty of this option is that you probably already own all the required hardware to test it out. All you will need is a cell phone, preferably one you would not mind losing. Modern cell phones are incredible devices, and they contain a multitude of sensors and processing capacity. Specifically phones provide a lot of the hardware capabilities that I am interested in for my scooter.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th><strong>Phone Hardware</strong></th>\n<th><strong>Specific Requirement</strong></th>\n<th><strong>Project Feature</strong></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>GPS radio</td>\n<td>Location tracking</td>\n<td>Tracking - Embedded</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cellular connection</td>\n<td>Data Transfer</td>\n<td>Tracking &#x26; Security</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Battery</td>\n<td>Remote Operation</td>\n<td>Tracking &#x26; Security</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Processor</td>\n<td>Handling App Logic</td>\n<td>Tracking &#x26; Security</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Speakers</td>\n<td>Alarm</td>\n<td>Security - Alarm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Accelerometers</td>\n<td>Detecting motion</td>\n<td>Security - Alarm</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>One requirement you will not see in the table above is locking.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>I can approach the locking issue in one of several ways:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Leave it out, who cares, the scooter will still have the alarm go off if someone does not unlock it.</li>\n<li>Add another device controlled by the phone (Arudino, raspberry pi, etc)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bluetooth_Low_Energy\">BLE</a> locking, with a lot of the electric scooters on the market you can connect to them via bluetooth and control the throttle via an app.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After some research, I ultimately chose that I wanted to go down the route of adding another device in addition to the cell phone.  figure out the locking capability. I will be using the ever popular <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ESP8266\">ESP8266</a>. I chose the ESP8266 because it is, cheap, popular, and includes WiFi connectivity.</p>\n<h3>‚öôÔ∏è Hardware Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Old, used Android phone, or cheap new one.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>For me, I am using an old busted moto x pure, the screen mostly works, and the battery life is crap, but it is good enough for testing.\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cellphone-47545d77a9d50c2509c5ce3cd3c3b5de-b2ab1.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"cellphone\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/cellphone-47545d77a9d50c2509c5ce3cd3c3b5de-f8fb9.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cellphone-47545d77a9d50c2509c5ce3cd3c3b5de-e8976.jpeg 148w,\n/static/cellphone-47545d77a9d50c2509c5ce3cd3c3b5de-63df2.jpeg 295w,\n/static/cellphone-47545d77a9d50c2509c5ce3cd3c3b5de-f8fb9.jpeg 590w,\n/static/cellphone-47545d77a9d50c2509c5ce3cd3c3b5de-85e3d.jpeg 885w,\n/static/cellphone-47545d77a9d50c2509c5ce3cd3c3b5de-d1924.jpeg 1180w,\n/static/cellphone-47545d77a9d50c2509c5ce3cd3c3b5de-b2ab1.jpeg 1620w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Pinfox-Waterproof-Electronic-Junction-Enclosure/dp/B06XSMK61Q/ref=sr_1_52?s=lamps-light&#x26;ie=UTF8&#x26;qid=1538679539&#x26;sr=1-52&#x26;keywords=project+box\">A water proof plastic project box</a> and mounting hardware.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mounting hardware: nuts, bolts, washers, and pipe straps. I needed to drill several holes to mount the pipe straps to the project box‚Äôs cover.\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-f5a3e.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"box1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-f8fb9.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-e8976.jpeg 148w,\n/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-63df2.jpeg 295w,\n/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-f8fb9.jpeg 590w,\n/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-85e3d.jpeg 885w,\n/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-d1924.jpeg 1180w,\n/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-9452e.jpeg 1770w,\n/static/box1-20f4b5d6964b05cbc932f03d2828d0a7-f5a3e.jpeg 3840w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-05d88.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 118.94273127753303%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"box2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-f8fb9.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-e8976.jpeg 148w,\n/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-63df2.jpeg 295w,\n/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-f8fb9.jpeg 590w,\n/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-85e3d.jpeg 885w,\n/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-d1924.jpeg 1180w,\n/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-9452e.jpeg 1770w,\n/static/box2-bdddfc16239cd4fe1f55c851a5ece61f-05d88.jpeg 1816w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-f5a3e.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"box3\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-f8fb9.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-e8976.jpeg 148w,\n/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-63df2.jpeg 295w,\n/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-f8fb9.jpeg 590w,\n/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-85e3d.jpeg 885w,\n/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-d1924.jpeg 1180w,\n/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-9452e.jpeg 1770w,\n/static/box3-40c8dda19c4debbef1b8a8ed55ac5ba5-f5a3e.jpeg 3840w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Cheap SIM card, <a href=\"https://www.freedompop.com/\">FreedomPop</a>, <a href=\"https://ting.com\">Ting</a>, <a href=\"https://hologram.io/\">Hologram</a> are good options.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s?k=esp8266&#x26;ref=nb_sb_noss_1\">esp8266</a> micro controller - Optional, needed for locking capability.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.sparkfun.com/products/15105\">Optoisolator</a> - to isolate the scooter which runs on 5v from the the esp8266 which runs on 3.3v.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>üíæ Software Requirements:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://llamalab.com/automate/\">Automate app</a> - for running a simple ‚Äúapp‚Äù on our phone.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.arduino.cc/en/main/software\">Arduino IDE</a>- for programming our esp8266.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>üì± Setup Cell Phone:</h3>\n<p>For my SIM card, I am using a spare <a href=\"https://www.freedompop.com/\">Freedom Pop</a> SIM.  Freedom pop offers limited data plans, some which are free if you do not go over your data cap. Since my scooter‚Äôs cell phone will use very little data, I shouldn‚Äôt have a problem staying within FreedomPop‚Äôs free tier.</p>\n<p>The first step I took was to reset the phone, so that it does not contain any personal data. I also created a throwaway email account for my scooter, because I needed an email address to be able to download apps from the play store. For tracking, I used google‚Äôs built in find my phone feature.</p>\n<p>The next step is to install the <a href=\"https://llamalab.com/automate/\">Automate app</a>, this app allows to you to create ‚Äúprograms‚Äù to automate different features of your phone. Using Automate‚Äôs visual flowchart interface, I made an app that will handle the logic for my scooter, you can find a copy of the app here:   insert link,  add to repo</p>\n<h3>The app‚Äôs logic works as such:</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>When it detects movement via the phone‚Äôs accelerometer:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The phone sends a http request to my scooterCheckSelf endpoint, to check to see if the scooter has been checked out.</li>\n<li>\n<p>My endpoint responds with true or false, letting our phone know if the scooter has been checked out.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>If the scooter has not been checked out,</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Turn on alarm and send http request to esp8266 to lock the throttle.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>If the scooter is checked out, </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Send http request to esp8266 to unlock the throttle.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Program esp8266</h3>\n<p>The phone and esp8266 will communicate via an Ad-hoc WiFi network. The esp8266 will act as an access point which the phone will connect to. Also the esp8266 will serve up a simple web server with which the phone will be able to send requests to.</p>\n<h3>To setup the esp8266:</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Download and install <a href=\"https://www.arduino.cc/en/Main/Software\">Arduino IDE</a></li>\n<li>Flash custom scooter controller firmware onto esp8266 - insert link\nadd to repo</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>The scooter controller firmware‚Äôs logic works as such:</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Creates an ad-hoc wifi network, that the cell phone will connect to.</li>\n<li>Prints it‚Äôs ip address to it‚Äôs serial port. </li>\n<li>\n<p>Creates a simple web server with two endpoints.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong><code class=\"language-text\">http://{esp8266‚Äôs IP address}/on</code></strong>  ‚Äî send high power to pin SD3 (known as pin 10 in code)</li>\n<li><strong><code class=\"language-text\">http://{esp8266‚Äôs IP address}/off</code></strong>  ‚Äî send low power to pin SD3</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>üîå Wiring Diagram</h3>\n<p>The actual model of esp8266 I used differs from the one in the diagram, so pin layout may vary.\nThe 4n35 optoisolator needs a resistor 470 ohm connected pin 1, the other side of the optoisolator interrupts the positive wire from the scooter‚Äôs head unit to the scooter‚Äôs throttle. </p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-a65ab.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 49.75845410628019%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"wiring simple\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-fb8a0.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-526de.png 885w,\n/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-08f6a.png 1770w,\n/static/wiring-simple-e1284afd2a176d40110d29c81798f07d-a65ab.png 2484w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><strong>Fritzing Wiring Diagram File:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/1zzq6pjopehvrqt/ESP8266Sketch%20%281%29.fzz?dl=0\">https://www.dropbox.com/s/1zzq6pjopehvrqt/ESP8266Sketch%20%281%29.fzz?dl=0</a></p>\n<h3>üçû Bread Board Test</h3>\n<p>You can consider the LED as a stand in for the throttle in this setup. Since the LED is on, the scooter would be unlocked.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-f5a3e.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 54.37499999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"breadboard\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-f8fb9.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-e8976.jpeg 148w,\n/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-63df2.jpeg 295w,\n/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-f8fb9.jpeg 590w,\n/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-85e3d.jpeg 885w,\n/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-d1924.jpeg 1180w,\n/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-9452e.jpeg 1770w,\n/static/breadboard-7689f706f96405046d644f4b1d7aad12-f5a3e.jpeg 3840w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>Mount Box to Scooter</h3>\n<p>The scooter in the photos is a cheap kick scooter for testing purposes. To test the throttle locking function I would need use an electric scooter, and I would need to route wires from the scooter‚Äôs head unit and throttle. Both the phone and esp8266 test rig are inside of the box.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-f5a3e.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"The project box is comically large because it is needed to hold my spare large phone. A smaller phone would be a better choice.\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-f8fb9.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-e8976.jpeg 148w,\n/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-63df2.jpeg 295w,\n/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-f8fb9.jpeg 590w,\n/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-85e3d.jpeg 885w,\n/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-d1924.jpeg 1180w,\n/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-9452e.jpeg 1770w,\n/static/kickscooter-43be571740e9178aa57798c682557472-f5a3e.jpeg 3840w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/kickscooter2-132fcda854f70b4755c7d1579f317360-b2ab1.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"kickscooter2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/kickscooter2-132fcda854f70b4755c7d1579f317360-f8fb9.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/kickscooter2-132fcda854f70b4755c7d1579f317360-e8976.jpeg 148w,\n/static/kickscooter2-132fcda854f70b4755c7d1579f317360-63df2.jpeg 295w,\n/static/kickscooter2-132fcda854f70b4755c7d1579f317360-f8fb9.jpeg 590w,\n/static/kickscooter2-132fcda854f70b4755c7d1579f317360-85e3d.jpeg 885w,\n/static/kickscooter2-132fcda854f70b4755c7d1579f317360-d1924.jpeg 1180w,\n/static/kickscooter2-132fcda854f70b4755c7d1579f317360-b2ab1.jpeg 1620w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The minimal effort option does work, I was able to get it to detect motion, control the alarm, lock status, and communicate with my API. Not a bad result for a mostly broken phone and a $5 micro controller. However I didn‚Äôt bother thoroughly testing this solution. I assume that I would have issues with battery life, managing sleep states and software stability. This option was a fun experiment in seeing how far I could go, without out putting much effort into the setup</p>\n<h2>The Embedded Option</h2>\n<p>For the embedded option, I made a video explaining how I put it together. The material below is written as supplementary material for the video, rather than an overview.\nInsert Link to Video</p>\n<p>Using off the shelf components, I will be putting together a custom device purpose built to work with my application. The embedded option is attempt to create a solution that would be somewhat plausible to deploy to actual customers. However there are certainly a lot of improvements that could be made. </p>\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Over the air updates - via Particle cloud service.</li>\n<li>More predictable results,  no unnecessary software running on our device. </li>\n<li>More customizable actions.</li>\n<li>Battery should last a lot longer.</li>\n<li>Better Tracking</li>\n<li>More compact than minimal option.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>More complicated assembly.</li>\n<li>Particle has a monthly cost.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Parts List:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.sparkfun.com/products/13740\">GPS Receiver - GP-20U7</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/1536\">Buzzer</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://store.particle.io/collections/cellular\">Particle Electron</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/ALITOVE-Female-Connector-WS2812B-SK6812-RGBW/dp/B071H5XCN5/ref=sr_1_39?crid=3FVLXSARLY7VV&#x26;keywords=jst+connector&#x26;qid=1548081502&#x26;sprefix=jst+co%2Caps%2C178&#x26;sr=8-39\">JST-SM Connectors</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/3931\">Waterproof Enclosure</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.sparkfun.com/products/15105\">Optoisolator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/2809\">LIS3DH Triple-Axis Accelerometer</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/1609\">Perma-Proto Half-sized Breadboard</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/598\">Female Pin Headers</a></li>\n<li>Typical electronics supplies: resistors, wire, solder, connectors</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>üíø Software List</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Custom Particle Firmware ‚Äî Insert Link</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Particle Firmware Flow</h3>\n<p><strong>Main Loop:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Check if battery status is below 10%, if so perma-lock scooter </li>\n<li>\n<p>Check if scooter has been has been unlocked longer than the ride time limit.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>If so, lock scooter.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li>Gather GPS data</li>\n<li>\n<p>Check for movement, </p>\n<ol>\n<li>If movement occurred, and scooter is locked, sound alarm.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li>Run google locator function, cell and wifi tracking.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>üîå Wiring Diagram</h3>\n<p>The particle electron is hidden to show the wiring.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-56152.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 62.96296296296296%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"wiring complex\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-fb8a0.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-526de.png 885w,\n/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-08f6a.png 1770w,\n/static/wiring-complex-95b0394b063b2e6881624e3ecb13421b-56152.png 2511w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/fe2phrqxk2ju1tk/ParticleSketchAccl-3.fzz?dl=0\">Fritzing Wiring Diagram File</a></p>\n<h3>‚úîÔ∏è Photos of completed device:</h3>\n<p>I cut the traces on the bottom of the board for: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Row 2 Column C </li>\n<li>Row 3, Column C</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/protoboard1-479aeebf1d04c9ce0c06f90783756cb0-c1266.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 72.75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: